        <div>
          <p class="font-mono text-[10px] text-[#888] dark:text-[#666] uppercase tracking-widest mb-1.5">About This Tool</p>
          <h2 id="about-heading" class="text-[20px] font-semibold text-[#171717] dark:text-[#ededed] tracking-[-0.5px] text-pretty">
            AI-Powered Phishing &amp; Spam Detection
          </h2>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white dark:bg-[#111111] rounded-xl border border-[#ebebeb] dark:border-[#2e2e2e] p-6
                    shadow-[0_1px_1px_rgba(0,0,0,0.02),0_2px_2px_rgba(0,0,0,0.04)]
                    space-y-4 text-[13px] text-[#4d4d4d] dark:text-[#a0a0a0] leading-relaxed">

          <p>Online threats have never been more sophisticated. Whether you're dealing with a suspicious <strong class="font-medium text-[#171717] dark:text-[#ededed]">phishing email</strong> in your inbox, a potentially malicious <strong class="font-medium text-[#171717] dark:text-[#ededed]">phishing link</strong> embedded in a text message, or an unexpected robocall from an unknown number, knowing what represents genuine <strong class="font-medium text-[#171717] dark:text-[#ededed]">spam risk</strong> has become an essential daily skill. <strong class="font-medium text-[#171717] dark:text-[#ededed]">Spam Detector</strong> is a free, AI-powered tool that analyses any content — emails, URLs, comments, or screenshots — and returns an instant spam risk score alongside a detailed breakdown of every phishing indicator and scam pattern detected.</p>

          <h3 class="text-[14px] font-semibold text-[#171717] dark:text-[#ededed] tracking-[-0.2px] pt-1">Four Detection Modes</h3>

          <p><strong class="font-medium text-[#171717] dark:text-[#ededed]">Email &amp; Text Analysis.</strong> Paste any email body or text message to surface <strong class="font-medium text-[#171717] dark:text-[#ededed]">phishing emails</strong>, advance-fee fraud, lottery scams, and unsolicited commercial messages. The AI identifies urgency language, impersonation signals, and suspicious phrasing that characterise <strong class="font-medium text-[#171717] dark:text-[#ededed]">potential spam</strong> with high accuracy.</p>

          <p><strong class="font-medium text-[#171717] dark:text-[#ededed]">Phishing Link Scanner.</strong> Enter any URL to verify whether it leads to a phishing site, a malicious redirect, or a legitimate destination. Modern <strong class="font-medium text-[#171717] dark:text-[#ededed]">phishing software</strong> generates thousands of lookalike domains daily, designed to steal credentials; our scanner flags typosquatting, URL shorteners hiding the true <strong class="font-medium text-[#171717] dark:text-[#ededed]">phishing link</strong> destination, and other deceptive patterns that conventional blacklists miss.</p>

          <p><strong class="font-medium text-[#171717] dark:text-[#ededed]">Comment &amp; Form Spam Filter.</strong> Businesses and developers can paste user-generated content to screen for bot activity, keyword stuffing, and promotional spam before it reaches their platform. The tool distinguishes authentic engagement from automated <strong class="font-medium text-[#171717] dark:text-[#ededed]">potential spam</strong> patterns driven by bots and hired click-farms.</p>

          <p><strong class="font-medium text-[#171717] dark:text-[#ededed]">Screenshot Analysis.</strong> Scam messages on mobile often arrive as screenshots forwarded by friends or family. Upload any image and our AI reads the text visually to detect <strong class="font-medium text-[#171717] dark:text-[#ededed]">potential spam</strong> and phishing indicators — no copy-pasting required, which is especially useful for reports of <strong class="font-medium text-[#171717] dark:text-[#ededed]">spam calls</strong> where a transcript screenshot is all you have.</p>

          <h3 class="text-[14px] font-semibold text-[#171717] dark:text-[#ededed] tracking-[-0.2px] pt-1">Understanding Your Spam Risk Score</h3>

          <p>Every analysis returns a <strong class="font-medium text-[#171717] dark:text-[#ededed]">spam risk</strong> score from 0 to 100. A score of 0–39 is <strong class="font-medium text-[#171717] dark:text-[#ededed]">Safe</strong> — no meaningful phishing or spam indicators found. A score of 40–69 is <strong class="font-medium text-[#171717] dark:text-[#ededed]">Suspicious</strong> — potential spam signals are present and the sender should be independently verified before you click any link or share information. A score of 70–100 is <strong class="font-medium text-[#171717] dark:text-[#ededed]">Dangerous</strong> — clear phishing or scam signals detected; do not interact. The tool also names the specific scam type — Phishing, Advance-Fee Fraud, Tech Support Scam, or Lottery Scam — and provides a one-sentence tip on how to avoid that threat category in future.</p>

          <h3 class="text-[14px] font-semibold text-[#171717] dark:text-[#ededed] tracking-[-0.2px] pt-1">Spam Calls and How to Block Them</h3>

          <p><strong class="font-medium text-[#171717] dark:text-[#ededed]">Spam calls</strong> have surged dramatically, with robocallers and fraudsters using spoofed numbers to impersonate banks, tax agencies, and technology companies. Our screenshot scan lets you analyse call transcripts or voicemail screenshots to determine whether a call is a live phishing attempt. For step-by-step instructions on <strong class="font-medium text-[#171717] dark:text-[#ededed]">how to block spam calls</strong> on Android and iPhone, visit the FAQ section below — we cover carrier-level blocking, native OS settings, and third-party apps.</p>

          <h3 class="text-[14px] font-semibold text-[#171717] dark:text-[#ededed] tracking-[-0.2px] pt-1">Why AI Beats Traditional Spam Filters</h3>

          <p>Static blacklists and rule-based filters struggle against modern <strong class="font-medium text-[#171717] dark:text-[#ededed]">phishing software</strong> that generates new domains and crafts novel phrasing daily, specifically engineered to evade keyword matching. This tool uses the OpenAI API to perform contextual, intent-aware analysis — understanding the meaning behind a message rather than just matching patterns — giving you accurate <strong class="font-medium text-[#171717] dark:text-[#ededed]">spam risk</strong> assessment even for targeted attacks that bypass conventional filters entirely. Whether you're an individual protecting your accounts, a developer building a safer product, or a business screening inbound communications for phishing and spam, this free tool delivers instant, actionable intelligence for any content that raises concern.</p>
        </div>
